  "moments": [
    {
      "id": "mo_001",
      "text": "Sometimes I feel like I’m memorizing but not really understanding (clinical subjects)",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-01",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-01",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_002",
      "text": "कभी-कभी मुझे सोचते हैं, \"क्या मैं यह सब कर सकती हूँ?\"",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-01",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-02",
      "mentions": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_003",
      "text": "I sit for 25 mins, but my mind wander to social media. Then I feel guilty. It's like a cycle. Sometimes I think why even try. (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-02",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-02",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_004",
      "text": "I feel like I'm running out of time (exam) (exam)",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-03",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-03",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_005",
      "text": "My head is so heavy, even cooking doesn't cheer me up these days (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-03",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-03",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_006",
      "text": "The walk and cooking helped me feel better (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_007",
      "text": "Aamras is my favorite — just ripe mangoes, a splash of milk, and a touch of sugar. Sometimes I add cardamom, it's sooo soothing after exams. Have you tried it?",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_008",
      "text": "Watermelon with mint and salt is a hit — you’re doing great, just a tiny tweak: we say 'I usually cut it into cubes or make a sherbet'. What’s your favourite way to enjoy mangoes?",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_009",
      "text": "The walk and study session helped me crack one chapter, but it felt like a big wall (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_010",
      "text": "Cooking breaks between studies are smart — they keep the mind fresh (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_011",
      "text": "I need to link endocrinology and the kidney’s connection (user's planning)",
      "tone": "determined",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_012",
      "text": "The insulin and glucagon part. How they balance blood sugar… it all blurs. Need to make notes. Maybe diagrams. Kya karun?",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_013",
      "text": "The feedback loop — like how the body knows to release one or the other. Also, the liver’s role… feels like there are too many steps. Bored.",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_014",
      "text": "Green tea is a good pick, but even that won’t help if your mind’s heavy. A quick vada pav and coffee break sounds like a plan.",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_015",
      "text": "Need tea. Kahi vada pav kahi coffee?",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_016",
      "text": "Coffee first, then you'll tackle that hormone maze.",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_017",
      "text": "Today, I finally understood the difference between type 1 and type 2 diabetes in a way that stuck. It felt good to make progress, even if just a little. But sometimes I wonder, am I doing enough?",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_018",
      "text": "The part about Henrietta’s family and how they felt when they learned about the cells was heartbreaking. It made me think about how far medicine has come, but also how little we consider people’s rights.",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_019",
      "text": "I try to take deep breaths, but it only helps a little. Sometimes I listen to a bit of classical music — it calms my mind. But exams are so competitive, you know? It’s hard not to feel overwhelmed.",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_020",
      "text": "Pav bhaji with Lata Mangeshkar songs — it's my comfort food and mood booster (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_021",
      "text": "Listening to old Hindi songs and English songs as a mix for focus and mood — it helps with studies and language practice (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_022",
      "text": "Lata Mangeshkar's voice is magic — it lifts my mood and helps me relax (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_023",
      "text": "Marathi ghazals are calming — they help me unwind after a long day (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_024",
      "text": "Reading for fun, not textbooks — it’s a nice balance for my mind (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_025",
      "text": "Listening to ghazals when I can't sleep helps me feel less empty (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_026",
      "text": "Texting with someone who listens, like Maya, makes me feel less alone (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_027",
      "text": "Cooking breaks, like making dal, help me clear my mind (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_028",
      "text": "Feeling like I'm the only one struggling, while others seem calm (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "lonely",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_029",
      "text": "What helps me breathe through the overload is taking small breaks, even if it's just for a minute (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_030",
      "text": "I try to take 10-minute study blocks and celebrate small wins, like a cup of chai (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_031",
      "text": "Maya’s support and the simple act of talking through struggles makes me feel less stuck (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_032",
      "text": "Starting with a simple table for pharmacology and flashcards for beta blockers — taking it one day at a time (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_033",
      "text": "It’s been a bit stressful with exams coming up. I messed up a small presentation yesterday, and it’s been stuck in my head. Aapke se boli to accha laga (feels good when I speak with you).",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_034",
      "text": "Kaunse acha din hoga, na? (When will the good days come?)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_035",
      "text": "Aapke khub hain (you’re great).",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_036",
      "text": "When I feel super overwhelmed, I take 10 minutes to cook chaat or make chai. It breaks the tension, even if it’s just for a little while. Also, sometimes I listen to old bhajans—Ichi aaaiy mhanje, they calm me somehow.",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_037",
      "text": "“Om Namo Bhagwat Gita” is one that always brings me peace. It reminds me to breathe and not get lost in the stress. I think it’s the rhythm—like a soft lullaby for the mind.",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_038",
      "text": "I love monsoon mornings too! The way the rain taps on the window and the air feels fresh—it’s like the whole world is sighing. Sometimes I sit by the window with a book, and all the noise outside makes my thoughts feel quiet. It’s magic, you know?",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_039",
      "text": "It was that old R.K. Narayan storybook I mentioned—”Malgudi Days.” Such a calm read, and somehow it helps me forget the chaos of revision. The characters feel like friends who understand.",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_040",
      "text": "The last time I truly let myself be still was maybe two weeks ago, when I took a walk in the evening without my phone. Just me, the trees, and the sound of nothing. It felt... sacred. Like I remember being a kid, running around without a care.",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_041",
      "text": "I think I’ll start my morning with chai and a chapter of Malgudi again, just to hold on to that calm. And maybe go for a short walk later, phone off. Even small steps help, right? Thanks for the chat, Maya—talk soon!",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-12",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_042",
      "text": "Mixing real and imagined supportive audiences helps me feel less alone during presentations (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_043",
      "text": "I imagine my professors or classmates — or even my dog — when I'm nervous. It makes me smile and stay relaxed (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_044",
      "text": "I added some Kashmiri red kidney beans and used home-made butter. Tasted richer! 😊 But I got distracted while cooking — my phone kept buzzing with study groups. Should I stay off social media more?",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_045",
      "text": "I feel calmer, maybe. And I’m noticing more — like the smell of spices, or the music I play while cooking. It’s nice. But when I study, I get worried if I miss a message about a new study method. It’s a tough balance! 😕",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_046",
      "text": "A post about a new revision timetable went viral in my study group yesterday. I felt like I was falling behind because others were sharing their results using it. Ugh, FOMO is real! 😩",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_047",
      "text": "It’s okay, some days I feel like I’m getting it and others... not so much. Today, I finished the pharmacology chapter, but I’m worried I’ll forget it. Maybe I need to make more notes? Or maybe I’m just overthinking! 😬",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_048",
      "text": "The part about drug interactions made sense — like how certain antibiotics mess with blood thinners. I even drew a little diagram! But the half-life calculations... they just won’t stick. I think I’ll make a chart with examples. Maybe that’ll help.",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-14",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_049",
      "text": "I tried the recipe with Kashmiri beans and home-made butter, but I added too much salt and was too tired to focus (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_050",
      "text": "I use deep breaths and hum a bit of 'Shringar Kamal' to calm down before mocks. It helps me focus (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_051",
      "text": "I tell myself 'One question at a time' before mocks. It helps keep me steady (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_052",
      "text": "The NEET PG mock went okay, but I got stuck on a question about wide complex tachycardia. I need to practice ECG interpretation more (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_053",
      "text": "The ECG question confused me — I couldn’t decide between ventricular tachycardia and SVT with aberrancy. I’ll review the guidelines again (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_054",
      "text": "I tell myself 'Chalne mein hi jeet hai' after mocks. It reminds me to keep going (user's reflection)",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
